**Overall Meaning:**

"One who practices [pranayama] for only one day is freed from all sins. A man who is devoted to breath control for three years or more..."

**Explanation:**

This verse from the Upanishads highlights the profound benefits of pranayama practice, suggesting that even a single day of dedicated practice can have a transformative effect on the practitioner. It also implies that continued dedication to pranayama over a longer period leads to even greater spiritual growth.

**Breakdown:**

* **"एकाहमात्रं कुर्वाणः":** This emphasizes that even practicing pranayama for just one day can have significant benefits.
* **"सर्वपापैः प्रमुच्यते":**  This highlights the purifying effect of pranayama, claiming it can free one from all sins.
* **"संवत्सरत्रयादूर्ध्वं":** This indicates that continued practice for three years or more yields even greater benefits.
* **"प्राणायामपरो नरः":** This describes a person who is dedicated to and focused on the practice of pranayama.

This verse emphasizes the transformative power of pranayama practice, suggesting that it can cleanse the mind and lead to spiritual progress, even with just a short-term commitment. It encourages individuals to cultivate a consistent practice for greater spiritual growth. 
